            <h2>Cross Country</h2>

            <p><strong>The Men's Cross Country team will be meeting to practice at the following times: </strong></p>
            <div class="well well-lg">
                <ul>
                    <li>Tuesdays and Thursdays meet at 5:30PM at the corner of Park & Langdon, we will then jog over to the track for a workout. (We have access to The Dan McClimon Memorial Track on Tuesdays from 6-7PM. Thursdays we will do a non-track workout.)</li>
                    <li>Mondays and Wednesdays meet at 5:30PM at the corner of Park & Langdon. (These are easy run days)</li>
                    <li>Fridays we have no official practice.</li>
                    <li>Saturdays are our race day!</li>
                    <li>Sundays are long runs, the time and place for Sunday practices will be posted on Facebook in our group.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <p><strong>The Women's Cross Country team will be meeting to practice at the following times: </strong></p>
            <div class="well well-lg">
                <ul>
                    <li>Tuesdays and Thursdays meet at 5:30PM at the corner of Park & Langdon (We have access to The Dan McClimon Memorial Track on Tuesdays from 6-7PM.)</li>
                    <li>Mondays and Wednesdays meet at 5:30PM at the corner of Park & Langdon.</li>
                    <li>Fridays are to be determined</li>
                    <li>Saturdays are our race day!</li>
                    <li>Sundays are long runs, the time and place for Sunday practices will be posted on Facebook in our group.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <p>For more information, please contact men's coach <a href="">Jim Reardon</a>, or women's coach <a href="">Sandy Gregorich</a>.
            <br />
            <br />
            WTC's Home Cross Country Course: Newly created in 2008, WTC's home cross country course is located on the rolling hills of <a href="">Pope Farm Park</a> in Middleton, WI (just west of Madison). The course currently has an <a href="">8k</a> Course as well as a <a href="">5k</a> Course.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
